wallpaper - command-line tool to set wallpaper using feh, written in haskell by alf

usage:
wallpaper [command] [args]

commands:
favorite [args]	
	Tag a wallpaper as favorite
	no args adds current wallpaper to favorites
	used with -r 'num' as args adds the 'num' most recent wallpaper to favorites

list [args]
	List wallpapers, numbering corresponds to set/clear commands (read below)
	--all/-a 	lists all available wallpapers
	--recent/-r	lists recent wallpapers
	--favorite/-f	lists favorite wallpapers

set [args]
	Set a wallpaper
	no args sets a random wallpaper (equivalent to `wallpaper set --random`)
	--favorite/-f 'num' 	set favorite number 'num' (see list)
	--recent/-r 'num' 	set recent number 'num'

clear [args]
	--favorite/-f	clear favorites
	--recent/-r	clear recent
